# DBRepair-Windows

Release notes for the Windows counterpart to DBRepair.sh (DBRepair-Windows.ps1)

# Release Info

v1.02.02
  - Add `replace` command to restore the databases from a saved backup (Plex's nightly backups or
    this tool's own), with integrity checking before swapping
  - Add `deflate` command to shrink a bloated main database
  - `prune` now also removes stale PMS temp files from the transcode cache

v1.02.01
  - Add Full-Text Search index checking and rebuild, folded into `check`, `reindex`, and `automatic`
  - Report FTS status in `status`

v1.02.00
  - Add `check`, `vacuum`, `repair`, `reindex`, `show`, `status`, and `undo` commands
  - Keep persistent timestamped backups so the last successful operation can be undone
  - Add free-space checks before destructive operations
  - `automatic` now checks the databases first and stops if they're damaged
  - Fix Plex SQLite path typos in the registry fallback

v1.01.02
  - Remove `statistics_bandwidth` pruning, as it's now part of PMS 1.41.8
  - Change `quit` to 98 and `exit` to 99
  - Minor logging refactoring

v1.01.01
  - Add `staticstics_bandwidth` pruning during automatic repair.

v1.01.00
  - Rename this tool to be compliant with Plex inc. Trademark Policy.

v1.00.02
  - Check whether PMS is running at more points in the process.
  - Don't remove temp files in scripted mode if the last operation failed.
  - Better export process that improves upon the UTF-8 fix in v1.00.01.

v1.00.01
  - Bug Fix: Ensure UTF-8 characters get exported/imported properly.

v1.00.00
  - Initial Windows PowerShell script release, aiming to provide a similar experience as DBRepair.sh, with command-name-based input.
  - Initial command support:
    - AUTO(matic)
    - EXIT
    - PRUN(e)
    - STAR(t)
    - STOP
